Methods
A longitudinal, population-based study was conducted among perinatal women giving birth at maternity facilities in Setagaya area of Tokyo, Japan. Of the 1775 women who participated, 1311 women met the inclusion criteria of this analysis. All data, including EPDS, were collected via self-administrated questionnaires at 20 weeks’ gestation and at 5 time points postpartum, from the first few days to 3 months postpartum. We divided EPDS items into three factors: “anxiety,” “anhedonia,” and “depression,” according to factor analysis.
